title.narrative: Strengthening Statistical Capacity and Informational Base for Evidence-Based Planning

description.narrative: The project development objective is to strengthen the statistical capacity and improve the informational base of the Recipient, in order to provide quality information, as defined by its reliability, timeliness, accuracy and representativeness with the level ofdisaggregation necessary to support systems for planning, designing, monitoring and evaluating public programs and policies.

title.narrative: List of Agricultural Production Units at the municipal level
GOB has updated quality statistical information that has been disseminated widely within the Government and among the public

target.value: Updated quality statistical information financed under the Project and disseminated widely within the Government and among thepublic.

actual.value: Under the original financing, statistical information was produced in the 4 components of the original project and itsdissemination was completed, including access to some micro-data, based on INE's dissemination data policy. Under the AF,statistical information was produced under the 3 components: Multi-Purpose Cartography, Economic and Social Statistics. Thesesurveys provided quality information, which implies that they complied with the attributes defined in the PDO. The Government hasrevised the scope and approach of the Economic Census and instead they are currently carrying out 2 surveys with representativesamples in the following areas: i) Industry, Trade and Services and ii) Micro and Small Economic Units. Additionally, INE isdeveloping the Time-Use Pilot survey which reveals details on how individuals spend their time over a specific period, informationthat is missing from standard household surveys.

title.narrative: 100% of physically demarcated and non-demarcated areas have updated cartographic information used in the preparation of the National Agricultural Census and the National Housing and Population Census
90% of departments have representative data on living standards
90% of dwellings accounted for in the National Population and Housing Census
95% of localities with population over 10,000 inhabitants have information on economic establishments.
The country has a Consumer Price Index Calculated based on an updated basket with a new base year
100% of departments have updated information on agricultural production and its destination.
100% of the departments have updated demographic and health information.
100% of the departments have updated socio-demographic information.
100% of departments have updated economic information (Agriculture, Industry, Trade & Services)
At least 30 public statistical units and enterprises, at the national and subnational level, of the country's Statistical System apply standardized methods of production of data developed by INE.
Nine capital cities, El Alto and rural areas have updated information on household incomes and structure of expenditures.
